<data><id>oai:pangaea.de:doi:10.1594/PANGAEA.890595</id><md:MetaData/md:citation/md:title>Absorbance measurements of total particulate and non-algal particulate matter during Heincke cruise HE448 in Sognefjord and Trondheimsfjord, Norway</md:MetaData/md:citation/md:title><md:MetaData/md:citation/md:supplementTo/md:title>Fjord light regime: Bio-optical variability, absorption budget, and hyperspectral light availability in Sognefjord and Trondheimsfjord, Norway</md:MetaData/md:citation/md:supplementTo/md:title><md:MetaData/md:abstract>Data presented are absorbance (Abs) measurements of total particulate (PA) and non-algal particulate (NAP) material. NAP Abs spectra were measured using the same filters upon bleaching with 90% sodium hypochlorite solution. Water samples were collected from near-surface (4m) and subsurface (close to observed deep chlorophyll maxima (DCM) depths. Near-surface samples were collected from Ferry-Box system (4HJena, Germany) and the DCM samples were collected from a SBE 911plus CTD system (SeaBird, USA). Water samples of varying volume (0.25 - 0.75 l), depending on water turbidity, were filtered onto 47 mm, pre-combusted, 0.7 &#956;m glass fiber filters (Whatman, GF/F) under low vacuum. Absorbance was measured following the Quantitative Filter Technique (QFT) using a spectrophotometer with integrating sphere (Cary 4000, Agilent Technologies, USA). Reference spectra were measured using wet filters (ultra pure water). Blanks provided are average of spectra measured over a day. Samples were measured in triplicates.</md:MetaData/md:abstract><md:MetaData/md:project/md:label /><md:MetaData/md:event/md:label /><md:MetaData/md:event/md:comment /><md:MetaData/md:license/md:label>CC-BY-3.0</md:MetaData/md:license/md:label><md:MetaData/md:additionalSearchableContent>Sample ID | Volume | Vol | 400 nm | Absorbance | Quantitative filter technique | 401 nm | 402 nm | 403 nm | 404 nm | 405 nm | 406 nm | 407 nm | 408 nm | 409 nm | 410 nm | 411 nm | 412 nm | 